news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income rises 22% to Rs 455 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT said in a regulatory filing that its gross leasing stood at 1.3 million square feet in the third quarter of FY23, taking cumulative leasing during April-December to 3.5 million square feet.

news.title: Home registrations in Kolkata jump 61% since stamp duty sop
news.para: However, the registrations in December 2022 was lower by 17% against December 2021. Homes of less than 500 sqft took the biggest hit with registrations down 33% in a year.

news.title: Director of real estate firm arrested from Mumbai for fraud
news.para: Police said Bansal and her husband were wanted in several high-profile white collar economic crimes, including the ‘Gurgaon-Manesar Industrial Model Township Land Grab Scam’ amounting to Rs 1,500 crore.

news.title: Haryana RERA directs ISH Realtors to refund buyer's money
news.para: The allottee had booked a commercial unit in ISH Realtors Private Limited’s Sector 109 project in September 2013. The developer had promised to deliver the unit in four years but failed to keep its commitment.

news.title: Godrej Properties buys 89 acres of land in Khalapur, Maharashtra
news.para: Spread across about 89 acres, the proposed project is located near Imagicaa Theme Park and is estimated to have a development potential of approximately 1.9 million sq ft of saleable area.

news.title: TVS Motor buys Rs 65 crore residential villa in Bengaluru
news.para: The residential villa, spread over 3923 sq ft with a total plot area of 9488 sq ft, is located on Billionaire street in Koramangala's third block.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints to sell 96,180 sq meters land to Shoden Developers for Rs 655 crore
news.para: The land admeasuring 96,180 sq meters at Kavesar, Thane is being sold to Shoden Developers, a group company of House of Hiranandani, for total consideration of Rs 655 crore.

news.title: Pay to fix unsafe buildings or face development ban: UK tells housing firms
news.para: Ministers want developers to sign a contract committing them to pay to fix buildings which have been classed as unsafe under new safety standards brought in following the Grenfell Tower fire in 2017 which killed 72 people.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's subsidiary to acquire 70% shares in Duqm Cement Project for $2.25 million
news.para: UltraTech Cement had reported a dip of 37.87 crore in its net consolidated profit during the quarter ended December 31, 2022. Its profit after tax (PAT) stood Rs 1,062.58 crore in Q3 FY23 as against Rs 1,710.14 crore it registered in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures posts Rs 3.25 crore net loss in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kamdhenu Ventures' net consolidated income stood at Rs 69.69 crore in Q3 FY23, a quarter-on-quarter growth of 8.08 per cent from Rs 64.48 crore it registered in the previous quarter of the financial year 2022-23.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit up 9.58% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Ajmera Realty's total consolidated income stood at Rs 80.57 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 14.87 per cent from Rs 70.14 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra CM announces 300 km metro network in two years
news.para: "We are working towards completing work on nearly 300km of metro network here which would be made operational in the next two years. The work on line 3 will also start soon,” said Shinde.

news.title: Cochin development body to digitalize rent collection
news.para: Once it is implemented, GCDA will be able to easily manage the allocation and renting-out of its shops, and create a database of its rent management using the software.

news.title: West Bengal set to amend land reforms act
news.para: It is likely to introduce a bill in the state assembly in the budget session. This bill is to garner revenue for the state exchequer as so far the land for commercial use was available for a 99-year lease.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC property tax kitty still 45% short of year's target
news.para: The targeted property tax collection for the year as announced in the civic budget 2022-23 by the BMC chief was Rs 7,000 crore. This means around 55% of the targeted property tax has been collected for the year.
